crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a sophisticated Remote Access Trojan (RAT) or C2 agent. It employs several advanced malware techniques, including dynamic API resolution via hashing (sub_1400036e3) to obscure the use of wininet.dll, ws2_32.dll, and advapi32.dll. The binary implements a persistent communication loop with a Command-and-Control (C2) server over HTTP (sub_140001baa), utilizing Base64 encoding for data exfiltration and command reception. A large command dispatcher (sub_14000609a) with over 70 branches handles remote tasks such as process enumeration (sub_14000de10), file system manipulation (sub_14000756e, sub_140006abe), and socket-based reverse shell activities (sub_14000bdee). Furthermore, the sample explicitly manipulates memory protections using VirtualProtect to set PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE (RWX) permissions (sub_1400102d0), a high-confidence indicator of shellcode execution or self-modifying code.
